label.value: larval apodeme

value.value: Apodeme that is part of the late embryo/larva. Apodemes are not a continuous structure, but are split into two halves. In the embryo, this break is visible laterally. In the larva, the dorsal and ventral halves in the thoracic and abdominal segments are staggered, with the dorsal part being posterior to the ventral one.

label.value: larval abdominal apodeme

value.value: Any abdominal apodeme of the larva.

label.value: larval intersegmental apodeme

value.value: Apodeme located at the boundary between two late embryonic/larval segments.

label.value: embryonic/larval abdominal intersegmental apodeme

value.value: Apodeme located at an abdominal segment boundary.

label.value: embryonic/larval abdominal 1-2 intersegmental apodeme

value.value: Larval apodeme found at the boundary between segments A1 and A2 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

value.value: Intersegmental apodeme of embryonic/larval segments A1-7. It is the insertion site for longitudinal and ventral oblique muscles of A1-7 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997, pg 172).
